04:57.436 --> 05:01.244
[SPEAKER_00]: SB 184 was signed into law May of 2024.

05:01.885 --> 05:18.820
[SPEAKER_00]: And in this new law, it created a new congestion fee of $3 a day on daily rental cars, which is estimated to bring in a new $57 million in FY26 before growing to over $110 million by 2050.

05:18.800 --> 05:34.782
[SPEAKER_00]: And in that law, it directed RTD front-range passenger rail and CDOT to collaborate to deliver on starter service for inner city passenger rail from Denver to Fort Collins by January, 2029.

05:34.963 --> 05:45.297
[SPEAKER_00]: It allowed the entities to contemplate three different ways to govern this collaborative to deliver passenger rail.

05:45.277 --> 05:52.487
[SPEAKER_00]: through either an IGA or a new Colorado Rail Authority or an altogether new legal authority.

05:52.507 --> 06:03.302
[SPEAKER_00]: And what the principles kind of rallied around early on was the concept of an IGA given that all the existing entities had the legal authority they needed to

06:03.282 --> 06:07.508
[SPEAKER_00]: govern the service and enter into the service through an IGA.

06:07.528 --> 06:21.049
[SPEAKER_00]: I would say that some previous board members from RTD during the process of this legislation were advocates for the new Colorado Rail Authority as a potential solution.

06:21.369 --> 06:30.283
[SPEAKER_00]: And that idea still has some merit, but the legislation did not create an appropriation to do a proper study on that concept.

06:30.343 --> 06:31.585
[SPEAKER_00]: So early on,

06:31.565 --> 06:42.745
[SPEAKER_00]: That concept was really only given a cursory look as it's a complicated endeavor that would have needed in appropriation to do a full analysis on that concept.

06:43.346 --> 06:49.036
[SPEAKER_00]: So it's just worth noting it's not that the principles decided that concept was without merit.

06:49.056 --> 06:55.868
[SPEAKER_00]: It just was something that would have needed far more resources to really explore that as a viable governance option.

06:58.362 --> 07:06.431
[SPEAKER_00]: Also in last year's legislative session, SP 230 pass, which is a new production fee on oil and gas extraction.

07:06.471 --> 07:13.298
[SPEAKER_00]: This law is forecasted in its first full year to bring in around $110 million.

07:14.820 --> 07:24.690
