08:25.859 --> 08:48.089
[SPEAKER_00]: the principles decided to bring on Diane is that one of the most successful collaboratives that the state of Colorado has seen was the renovation and revitalization of Union Station, which required a lot of coordination among many different public entities to come together to come up with the creative financing mechanism to get that done.

08:48.109 --> 08:52.255
[SPEAKER_00]: And Diane led that project for then Mayor Hickenlooper as the first chief

08:52.235 --> 09:04.202
[SPEAKER_00]: project officer and so we're very blessed for her to come out of retirement to come lead this and do it again because it is a herculean effort to coordinate this many public entities with their own.

09:04.570 --> 09:08.936
[SPEAKER_00]: policies, bylaws, and enabling legislation.

09:09.216 --> 09:23.336
[SPEAKER_00]: And so there really is truly no one better to do this work than Diane, which then led to the March 1st report that had an initial cost estimate in review of available revenue streams and review of governance models.

09:23.777 --> 09:34.071
[SPEAKER_00]: And so we'll review a little bit of what the March 1st report said, but succinctly it said that there is enough existing resources

09:34.051 --> 09:38.821
